  "manual": [
    {
      "families": ["Charter"],
      "hint": "No stable open bundle in this script; add a licensed Charter-compatible .otf/.ttf (e.g. from your OS or a foundry) under fonts/bundled/charter/."
    },
    {
      "families": ["HK Grotesk"],
      "hint": "Not on Google Webfonts Helper; download from the rights holder (e.g. Hanken Design Co. / Fontshare) and drop .otf/.ttf into fonts/bundled/hk-grotesk/."
    },
    {
      "families": ["Luciole", "Luciole Math"],
      "hint": "Official zips from https://www.luciole-en-ligne.fr/ (or French government open-data mirrors)."
    },
    {
      "families": ["Reforma 1918", "Reforma 1969", "Reforma 2018"],
      "hint": "PampaType distributes Reforma behind a login; obtain files legally and place under fonts/bundled/reforma/."
    },
    {
      "families": ["MOESongUN", "TW-MOE-Std-Kai"],
      "hint": "Taiwan MOE fonts — follow MOE license terms; copy into fonts/bundled/."
    },
    {
      "families": ["Infini", "Infini Picto"],
      "hint": "CNAP Infini — check license; add manually if redistribution is allowed."
    },
    {
      "families": ["Twitter Color Emoji"],
      "hint": "Optional COLR emoji (e.g. twemoji-color-font releases); large; add only if you need it."
    },
    {
      "families": ["VG5000"],
      "hint": "Velvetyne VG5000 — download from velvetyne.fr if license fits your app."
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Typst also embeds Libertinus Serif, New Computer Modern, and DejaVu Sans Mono via the typst-assets crate; files here may duplicate those faces.",
    "Adobe Source Sans / Serif zips use current family names in font metadata (e.g. “Source Sans 3”); use #set text(font: \"…\") with the name Typst lists via list_typst_font_faces.",
    "Source Sans Pro / Source Serif Pro in your list: older documents used those strings; after bundling, pick the exact family name from the in-app font picker (Ag / font list)."
  ]
}
